snippet.textDisplay:
Feel like I missed an opportunity here. I hope this comment gets read. You interview tons of mainstream athletes (football, basketball, wrestling, etc.). Do you think you'll ever get a professional strongman on the show? They do food challenges ALL. THE. TIME. I feel like it would probably be pretty easy to get one of them on the show. They've all got great personalities and it would be great for the visibility of a sport that's been around forever, but has never made it mainstream. Hafthor Julius Bjornnson aka "The Mountain" from GoT aka Thor, Martins Licis the 2019 World's Strongest Man, Eddie Hall, Robert Oberst, the Stoltman Brothers? So many great athletes that LOVE eating.

Love the show. No complaints whatsoever about your guests. Pro tip for the haters, if you don't like a guest, don't watch the episode ;) That's what I do. Or sometimes I do watch guests I'm not familiar with and realize I like them more than I thought I would.
